# Agent workflow

## DRY
- Do not duplicate logic, components, or data structures — reuse existing abstractions (see `dry-rules.mdc`).
- Extend existing components and helpers before creating new ones.

## Migrations
- **Never run migrations** (`make mm`, `make m`, `tortoise migrate`, etc.) unless the user explicitly asks.
- When models change, describe what migration is needed — let the user run it.

## Tests
- **Never run tests** unless the user explicitly asks.
- Do not add tests unless requested or they provide meaningful coverage of real behavior.
